-- 131: Seed universal_stream_trade_signals from the locked v10 CSV.
--
-- Decomposes the 152 per-trade × per-row signal columns (38 trades × 4
-- signal types) into 1,422 (seq, trade_slug, signal_type) rows. Only ✓
-- cells emit a row; empty cells produce no row (absence IS the signal).
--
-- Split from migration 130 per Spec 42 §6.6.B seed migration contract.
-- Generated by _tmp_phase_b_seed_signals.mjs from the same v10 CSV that
-- seeds the catalog (migration 129). The generator enforces:
--   * CSV preflight (110 × 174)
--   * Spec 84 §8.5 v10 invariants (seq 50 excavation column-alignment fix,
--     realtor signal presence)
--   * Idempotent ON CONFLICT (seq, trade_slug, signal_type) DO NOTHING
--
-- Distribution: 1,295 bid + 51 work + 38 fallback + 38 last_minute = 1,422
-- across 38 unique trades. Phase F forecast engine queries this for
-- granular bimodal routing per (current_seq, trade).
--
-- Coverage by seq: 74 of the 110 catalog seqs carry at least one signal.
-- The 36 absent seqs are intentional per the v10 CSV design — they
-- correspond to states where no trade is bidding or working:
--   * seq 9         — Deferred (CoA hearing pause)
--   * seq 13        — Refused (CoA decision)
--   * seq 16-18     — Appeals in progress (work suspended pending appeal)
--   * seq 19-22     — CoA closure terminals (Withdrawn/Cancelled/Complete/Closed)
--   * seq 34-40     — Permit Notice & Response (notice issued / on hold /
--                     response received — no construction during these states)
--   * seq 91-98     — BP7 wind-down / Closure (Pending Closed, Closed, etc.)
--   * seq 99-110    — Dead states (Refusal, Abandoned, Revoked, VIOLATION,
--                     Order Issued, Cancelled, Follow-up Required)
--
-- An absent (seq, trade_slug, signal_type) row means the forecast engine
-- finds no row to route on for that lead at that stage — which is the
-- correct behavior for dead/closure/pause states (no trade should be
-- bidding or working there). This is NOT a missing-data bug.
--
-- Note: prior v9 CSV count comments in Spec 42 §6.6.B (1,710 bid + 51 work
-- + 38 fallback + 38 last_minute = 1,837) are out-of-date — they predate
-- the Phase A R0.6 BUG fixes that locked the v10 source. v10 counts are
-- what this seed reflects.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- UP
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- ─── Prerequisite: seed the 17 trades that v10 introduces ────────────
-- Migration 004 + migration 118 together seed 21 of the 38 trade slugs
-- referenced by the v10 Universal Stream. The remaining 17 (interior
-- finish trades, outdoor work, specialty) must exist BEFORE the signal
-- INSERTs below because universal_stream_trade_signals.trade_slug has
-- an FK to trades(slug). The runner wraps this whole file in a single
-- BEGIN/COMMIT, so the trade INSERTs and signal INSERTs land atomically.
--
-- ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING — re-runs are safe; any operator-added
-- name/icon/color overrides are preserved. sort_order continues from
-- migration 118's realtor at 33 (21 + realtor at 33 = ranges 21-33; the
-- new 17 take 34-50).
--
-- CI catch: the `db-tests` workflow runs all migrations against a fresh
-- testcontainer; this migration originally failed with FK violations on
-- the missing trades. Discovered in commit cd6d667 + R8 review.
ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;

-- ─── Universal stream trade signals (1,422 rows from v10) ────────────
ON CONFLICT (seq, trade_slug, signal_type) DO NOTHING;

ON CONFLICT (seq, trade_slug, signal_type) DO NOTHING;

ON CONFLICT (seq, trade_slug, signal_type) DO NOTHING;

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- DOWN — manual rollback only, intentionally not transactional
-- (Rule 6 / commit 8b1c10b)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Reverting this migration empties the signal table. Table from
-- migration 130 remains. Phase F forecast engine (when wired) falls back
-- to legacy PHASE_ORDINAL routing.
--
-- To roll back manually:
--
--   DELETE FROM universal_stream_trade_signals;
--
-- Re-running migration 131 restores the 1,422 rows.
